Course assessment

The prerequisites for positive result are:
1. 100% participation in (auditory) seminars;
2. to listen all e-lectures; 
3. to conduct all lecture tests (self-control tests) at a maximum score (100%) in the Moodle, the number to perform tests is not limited; 
4. to visit family practice centre and complete observation diary;
5. to perform the group-work presentation for the seminar "Upper respiratory tract infections";
6. to perform the practical assignment in the practical skills seminar;
7. The final test in the Moodle`i consists of 10 questions and cover both lecture and seminar materials. It must be performed at least 80% score. The number of performance is one time. The time for taking the test is 20 minutes and it is pre determined (see the schedule of your group) and the test cannot be taken at another time. You take the test at home one time during the given time.

The final grade is transferred to ÕIS the day after the final exam.

The first re-evaluation takes place at a pre-arranged time, usually one week after the first final exam. For this purpose, all work that was not submitted for regular evaluation or that did not meet the requirements must be submitted and the final test with a negative result must be retaken.

The second re-evaluation takes place at the end of the semester.
